6.20	Escallonia	Escallonia	Escallonia is a genus of 40-50 species of flowering plants of the Escalloniaceae family. Mostly evergreen shrubs but rarely small trees. Originally from South America. Commonly used as a hedging plant, it grows about 1 ft per year, and reaches between 4-8 ft in height. It is happy in coastal areas, but not very tolerant of dry winds.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/25/Escallonia-virgata-close.jpg/220px-Escallonia-virgata-close.jpg
